ce:section.ce:para:
First, to construct the sensor array, four types of CDs were synthesized by briefly mixing diphosphorus pentoxide, different amino acids and water within 60 s (Fig. 1
                        A). As shown in Fig. 1B, these four types of CDs exhibit maxima emission at around 440 nm and emitting blue fluorescence under 365 nm UV light illumination. This may be related to the sizes and their surface defects of the CDs, which was in consistent with the previous report [25]. In addition, all these four types of CDs display a typical excitation-dependent fluorescence behavior (Fig. 2
                        ). The fluorescence emission peaks of these CDs shifted from approximately 350 to 450 nm with an increasing excitation wavelengths from 300 to 460 nm. The quantum yield (QY) of these four types of CDs were measured to be 8.6% (CDs-1), 8.1% (CDs-2), 9.5% (CDs-3) and 8.9% (CDs-4), using quinine sulfate as the reference.
